main event: On June 23, 1953, two objects were observed in the sky over Key West, Florida for approximately 5 minutes.
interesting points: The objects exhibited erratic motion and were estimated to be 600 feet in dimension., One witness described the objects as similar in appearance to a bright star but with unusual oscillation and intensity changes., Witnesses reported that the objects disappeared behind a distant cloud., No physical evidence or sound was associated with the sighting., This incident was reported to the U.S. Air Force on October 1952, leading to analysis by Project Blue Book.
witness description: Two were navigators and one was a chief radio electrician with the U.S. Navy.
